Swarm mode: autonomous-development
Objective: Adopt Anthropic agent patterns in the swarm planner/controller.

Read the full spec at docs/superpowers/specs/auto-2026-03-15-review-for-architectural-patterns-autodev-s-planner-controll.md before starting.

Implementation priorities (in order):

1. DECISION VALIDATION GATE: Add _validate_decisions() to DrivingPlanner in swarm/planner.py. Rule-based checks: file overlap (use overlap.py), duplicate tasks (>80% title similarity), spawn budget enforcement, empty prompt rejection, circular dependency detection. Call before execute_decisions(). All algorithmic, no LLM.

2. CYCLE EVALUATOR: Create src/autodev/swarm/evaluator.py with CycleEvaluator and CycleGrade dataclass. Grade cycles on task_quality_score, agent_utilization_score, convergence_score. Inject feedback into planner prompt. All algorithmic scoring.

3. TWO-STEP PLANNER CHAIN: Split single planner LLM call into analysis step + decision step with gate between. Add ANALYSIS_PROMPT_TEMPLATE and DECISION_FROM_ANALYSIS_PROMPT to prompts.py. Add two_step_planning config flag to SwarmConfig. Fallback to single-call on parse failure.

4. WORKER OUTPUT VALIDATION: Add _validate_ad_result() to SwarmController. Validate status, summary, files_changed, discoveries, commits fields. Coerce malformed data. Log warnings. Integrate in _handle_agent_death().

5. PROMPT ENGINEERING: Add step-by-step reasoning block, negative examples (common mistakes), and 2-3 few-shot examples to prompts.py. Keep total growth under 500 tokens.

6. FAILURE REFLECTION: Add add_reflection() to SwarmLearnings. When same task fails 2+ times, construct structured reflection (was description clear? right role? deps satisfied?). Surface in planner prompt.

7. TESTS: test_decision_validation.py (overlap, duplicates, budget, empty prompt, circular deps), test_cycle_evaluator.py (high/low quality cycles, convergence, history), test_ad_result_validation.py (coercion, defaults), test_two_step_planner.py (analysis+decision flow, fallback), test_learnings.py (reflection). All existing tests must pass.

